{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":735,"text":"How many of you are creatives,"},{"time":3048,"text":"designers, engineers,\nentrepreneurs, artists,"},{"time":6696,"text":"or maybe you just have\na really big imagination?"},{"time":9107,"text":"Show of hands? (Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10979,"text":"That's most of you."},{"time":13334,"text":"I have some news for us creatives."},{"time":16714,"text":"Over the course of the next 20 years,"},{"time":21471,"text":"more will change around\nthe way we do our work"},{"time":25382,"text":"than has happened in the last 2,000."},{"time":28511,"text":"In fact, I think we're at the dawn\nof a new age in human history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33645,"text":"Now, there have been four major historical\neras defined by the way we work."},{"time":39404,"text":"The Hunter-Gatherer Age\nlasted several million years."},{"time":43163,"text":"And then the Agricultural Age\nlasted several thousand years."},{"time":47195,"text":"The Industrial Age lasted\na couple of centuries."},{"time":50709,"text":"And now the Information Age\nhas lasted just a few decades."},{"time":55020,"text":"And now today, we're on the cusp\nof our next great era as a species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61296,"text":"Welcome to the Augmented Age."},{"time":64000,"text":"In this new era, your natural human\ncapabilities are going to be augmented"},{"time":67717,"text":"by computational systems\nthat help you think,"},{"time":70809,"text":"robotic systems that help you make,"},{"time":73019,"text":"and a digital nervous system"},{"time":74691,"text":"that connects you to the world\nfar beyond your natural senses."},{"time":79437,"text":"Let's start with cognitive augmentation."},{"time":81403,"text":"How many of you are augmented cyborgs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84133,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86807,"text":"I would actually argue\nthat we're already augmented."},{"time":90288,"text":"Imagine you're at a party,"},{"time":91816,"text":"and somebody asks you a question\nthat you don't know the answer to."},{"time":95360,"text":"If you have one of these,\nin a few seconds, you can know the answer."},{"time":99869,"text":"But this is just a primitive beginning."},{"time":102863,"text":"Even Siri is just a passive tool."},{"time":106660,"text":"In fact, for the last\nthree-and-a-half million years,"},{"time":110065,"text":"the tools that we've had\nhave been completely passive."},{"time":114203,"text":"They do exactly what we tell them\nand nothing more."},{"time":117882,"text":"Our very first tool only cut\nwhere we struck it."},{"time":121822,"text":"The chisel only carves\nwhere the artist points it."},{"time":125343,"text":"And even our most advanced tools\ndo nothing without our explicit direction."},{"time":131008,"text":"In fact, to date, and this\nis something that frustrates me,"},{"time":134213,"text":"we've always been limited"},{"time":135685,"text":"by this need to manually\npush our wills into our tools --"},{"time":139210,"text":"like, manual,\nliterally using our hands,"},{"time":141531,"text":"even with computers."},{"time":144072,"text":"But I'm more like Scotty in \"Star Trek.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":146559,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148433,"text":"I want to have a conversation\nwith a computer."},{"time":150603,"text":"I want to say, \"Computer,\nlet's design a car,\""},{"time":153597,"text":"and the computer shows me a car."},{"time":155160,"text":"And I say, \"No, more fast-looking,\nand less German,\""},{"time":157792,"text":"and bang, the computer shows me an option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159979,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162208,"text":"That conversation might be\na little ways off,"},{"time":164538,"text":"probably less than many of us think,"},{"time":167227,"text":"but right now,"},{"time":169014,"text":"we're working on it."},{"time":170189,"text":"Tools are making this leap\nfrom being passive to being generative."},{"time":174831,"text":"Generative design tools\nuse a computer and algorithms"},{"time":178163,"text":"to synthesize geometry"},{"time":180795,"text":"to come up with new designs\nall by themselves."},{"time":183996,"text":"All it needs are your goals\nand your constraints."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186768,"text":"I'll give you an example."},{"time":188200,"text":"In the case of this aerial drone chassis,"},{"time":191012,"text":"all you would need to do\nis tell it something like,"},{"time":193662,"text":"it has four propellers,"},{"time":194959,"text":"you want it to be\nas lightweight as possible,"},{"time":197114,"text":"and you need it to be\naerodynamically efficient."},{"time":199408,"text":"Then what the computer does\nis it explores the entire solution space:"},{"time":204346,"text":"every single possibility that solves\nand meets your criteria --"},{"time":208297,"text":"millions of them."},{"time":209763,"text":"It takes big computers to do this."},{"time":211762,"text":"But it comes back to us with designs"},{"time":213741,"text":"that we, by ourselves,\nnever could've imagined."},{"time":217326,"text":"And the computer's coming up\nwith this stuff all by itself --"},{"time":220262,"text":"no one ever drew anything,"},{"time":221964,"text":"and it started completely from scratch."},{"time":225038,"text":"And by the way, it's no accident"},{"time":227449,"text":"that the drone body looks just like\nthe pelvis of a flying squirrel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231287,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234040,"text":"It's because the algorithms\nare designed to work"},{"time":236366,"text":"the same way evolution does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238715,"text":"What's exciting is we're starting\nto see this technology"},{"time":241399,"text":"out in the real world."},{"time":242582,"text":"We've been working with Airbus\nfor a couple of years"},{"time":245058,"text":"on this concept plane for the future."},{"time":246991,"text":"It's a ways out still."},{"time":249085,"text":"But just recently we used\na generative-design AI"},{"time":252889,"text":"to come up with this."},{"time":255609,"text":"This is a 3D-printed cabin partition\nthat's been designed by a computer."},{"time":260786,"text":"It's stronger than the original\nyet half the weight,"},{"time":263634,"text":"and it will be flying\nin the Airbus A320 later this year."},{"time":267405,"text":"So computers can now generate;"},{"time":268988,"text":"they can come up with their own solutions\nto our well-defined problems."},{"time":274677,"text":"But they're not intuitive."},{"time":276011,"text":"They still have to start from scratch\nevery single time,"},{"time":279121,"text":"and that's because they never learn."},{"time":282368,"text":"Unlike Maggie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284158,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285763,"text":"Maggie's actually smarter\nthan our most advanced design tools."},{"time":289467,"text":"What do I mean by that?"},{"time":290931,"text":"If her owner picks up that leash,"},{"time":292545,"text":"Maggie knows with a fair\ndegree of certainty"},{"time":294637,"text":"it's time to go for a walk."},{"time":296065,"text":"And how did she learn?"},{"time":297274,"text":"Well, every time the owner picked up\nthe leash, they went for a walk."},{"time":300622,"text":"And Maggie did three things:"},{"time":302524,"text":"she had to pay attention,"},{"time":304417,"text":"she had to remember what happened"},{"time":306523,"text":"and she had to retain and create\na pattern in her mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311429,"text":"Interestingly, that's exactly what"},{"time":313548,"text":"computer scientists\nhave been trying to get AIs to do"},{"time":316095,"text":"for the last 60 or so years."},{"time":318683,"text":"Back in 1952,"},{"time":320056,"text":"they built this computer\nthat could play Tic-Tac-Toe."},{"time":325081,"text":"Big deal."},{"time":327029,"text":"Then 45 years later, in 1997,"},{"time":330053,"text":"Deep Blue beats Kasparov at chess."},{"time":334046,"text":"2011, Watson beats these two\nhumans at Jeopardy,"},{"time":339038,"text":"which is much harder for a computer\nto play than chess is."},{"time":341990,"text":"In fact, rather than working\nfrom predefined recipes,"},{"time":345826,"text":"Watson had to use reasoning\nto overcome his human opponents."},{"time":350393,"text":"And then a couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":352856,"text":"DeepMind's AlphaGo beats\nthe world's best human at Go,"},{"time":357142,"text":"which is the most difficult\ngame that we have."},{"time":359378,"text":"In fact, in Go, there are more\npossible moves"},{"time":362298,"text":"than there are atoms in the universe."},{"time":366210,"text":"So in order to win,"},{"time":368060,"text":"what AlphaGo had to do\nwas develop intuition."},{"time":371098,"text":"And in fact, at some points,\nAlphaGo's programmers didn't understand"},{"time":375232,"text":"why AlphaGo was doing what it was doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379451,"text":"And things are moving really fast."},{"time":381135,"text":"I mean, consider --\nin the space of a human lifetime,"},{"time":384386,"text":"computers have gone from a child's game"},{"time":387920,"text":"to what's recognized as the pinnacle\nof strategic thought."},{"time":391999,"text":"What's basically happening"},{"time":394440,"text":"is computers are going\nfrom being like Spock"},{"time":397774,"text":"to being a lot more like Kirk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399747,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403389,"text":"Right? From pure logic to intuition."},{"time":408184,"text":"Would you cross this bridge?"},{"time":410609,"text":"Most of you are saying, \"Oh, hell no!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":412956,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":414288,"text":"And you arrived at that decision\nin a split second."},{"time":416969,"text":"You just sort of knew\nthat bridge was unsafe."},{"time":419421,"text":"And that's exactly the kind of intuition"},{"time":421434,"text":"that our deep-learning systems\nare starting to develop right now."},{"time":425722,"text":"Very soon, you'll literally be able"},{"time":427453,"text":"to show something you've made,\nyou've designed,"},{"time":429683,"text":"to a computer,"},{"time":430860,"text":"and it will look at it and say,"},{"time":432373,"text":"\"Sorry, homie, that'll never work.\nYou have to try again.\""},{"time":435854,"text":"Or you could ask it if people\nare going to like your next song,"},{"time":439773,"text":"or your next flavor of ice cream."},{"time":443549,"text":"Or, much more importantly,"},{"time":446152,"text":"you could work with a computer\nto solve a problem"},{"time":448540,"text":"that we've never faced before."},{"time":450201,"text":"For instance, climate change."},{"time":451626,"text":"We're not doing a very\ngood job on our own,"},{"time":453670,"text":"we could certainly use\nall the help we can get."},{"time":455939,"text":"That's what I'm talking about,"},{"time":457421,"text":"technology amplifying\nour cognitive abilities"},{"time":460000,"text":"so we can imagine and design things\nthat were simply out of our reach"},{"time":463576,"text":"as plain old un-augmented humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467984,"text":"So what about making\nall of this crazy new stuff"},{"time":470949,"text":"that we're going to invent and design?"},{"time":473952,"text":"I think the era of human augmentation\nis as much about the physical world"},{"time":478069,"text":"as it is about the virtual,\nintellectual realm."},{"time":481833,"text":"How will technology augment us?"},{"time":484261,"text":"In the physical world, robotic systems."},{"time":487620,"text":"OK, there's certainly a fear"},{"time":489380,"text":"that robots are going to take\njobs away from humans,"},{"time":491892,"text":"and that is true in certain sectors."},{"time":494174,"text":"But I'm much more interested in this idea"},{"time":497076,"text":"that humans and robots working together\nare going to augment each other,"},{"time":502110,"text":"and start to inhabit a new space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504192,"text":"This is our applied research lab\nin San Francisco,"},{"time":506578,"text":"where one of our areas of focus\nis advanced robotics,"},{"time":509744,"text":"specifically, human-robot collaboration."},{"time":513034,"text":"And this is Bishop, one of our robots."},{"time":515817,"text":"As an experiment, we set it up"},{"time":517630,"text":"to help a person working in construction\ndoing repetitive tasks --"},{"time":521984,"text":"tasks like cutting out holes for outlets\nor light switches in drywall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526202,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529877,"text":"So, Bishop's human partner\ncan tell what to do in plain English"},{"time":533012,"text":"and with simple gestures,"},{"time":534341,"text":"kind of like talking to a dog,"},{"time":535812,"text":"and then Bishop executes\non those instructions"},{"time":537979,"text":"with perfect precision."},{"time":539895,"text":"We're using the human\nfor what the human is good at:"},{"time":542908,"text":"awareness, perception and decision making."},{"time":545265,"text":"And we're using the robot\nfor what it's good at:"},{"time":547529,"text":"precision and repetitiveness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550252,"text":"Here's another cool project\nthat Bishop worked on."},{"time":552643,"text":"The goal of this project,\nwhich we called the HIVE,"},{"time":555742,"text":"was to prototype the experience\nof humans, computers and robots"},{"time":559617,"text":"all working together to solve\na highly complex design problem."},{"time":563793,"text":"The humans acted as labor."},{"time":565268,"text":"They cruised around the construction site,\nthey manipulated the bamboo --"},{"time":568765,"text":"which, by the way,\nbecause it's a non-isomorphic material,"},{"time":571545,"text":"is super hard for robots to deal with."},{"time":573443,"text":"But then the robots\ndid this fiber winding,"},{"time":575489,"text":"which was almost impossible\nfor a human to do."},{"time":577964,"text":"And then we had an AI\nthat was controlling everything."},{"time":581609,"text":"It was telling the humans what to do,\ntelling the robots what to do"},{"time":584923,"text":"and keeping track of thousands\nof individual components."},{"time":587862,"text":"What's interesting is,"},{"time":589066,"text":"building this pavilion\nwas simply not possible"},{"time":592231,"text":"without human, robot and AI\naugmenting each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597890,"text":"OK, I'll share one more project.\nThis one's a little bit crazy."},{"time":601234,"text":"We're working with Amsterdam-based artist\nJoris Laarman and his team at MX3D"},{"time":605726,"text":"to generatively design\nand robotically print"},{"time":608628,"text":"the world's first autonomously\nmanufactured bridge."},{"time":612315,"text":"So, Joris and an AI are designing\nthis thing right now, as we speak,"},{"time":616024,"text":"in Amsterdam."},{"time":617220,"text":"And when they're done,\nwe're going to hit \"Go,\""},{"time":619565,"text":"and robots will start 3D printing\nin stainless steel,"},{"time":622900,"text":"and then they're going to keep printing,\nwithout human intervention,"},{"time":626207,"text":"until the bridge is finished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629099,"text":"So, as computers are going\nto augment our ability"},{"time":632051,"text":"to imagine and design new stuff,"},{"time":634225,"text":"robotic systems are going to help us\nbuild and make things"},{"time":637144,"text":"that we've never been able to make before."},{"time":640347,"text":"But what about our ability\nto sense and control these things?"},{"time":644531,"text":"What about a nervous system\nfor the things that we make?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648586,"text":"Our nervous system,\nthe human nervous system,"},{"time":651122,"text":"tells us everything\nthat's going on around us."},{"time":654186,"text":"But the nervous system of the things\nwe make is rudimentary at best."},{"time":657894,"text":"For instance, a car doesn't tell\nthe city's public works department"},{"time":661481,"text":"that it just hit a pothole at the corner\nof Broadway and Morrison."},{"time":664635,"text":"A building doesn't tell its designers"},{"time":666691,"text":"whether or not the people inside\nlike being there,"},{"time":669399,"text":"and the toy manufacturer doesn't know"},{"time":672433,"text":"if a toy is actually being played with --"},{"time":674464,"text":"how and where and whether\nor not it's any fun."},{"time":677620,"text":"Look, I'm sure that the designers\nimagined this lifestyle for Barbie"},{"time":681458,"text":"when they designed her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682706,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684177,"text":"But what if it turns out that Barbie's\nactually really lonely?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":687107,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691266,"text":"If the designers had known"},{"time":692578,"text":"what was really happening\nin the real world"},{"time":694709,"text":"with their designs -- the road,\nthe building, Barbie --"},{"time":697316,"text":"they could've used that knowledge\nto create an experience"},{"time":700034,"text":"that was better for the user."},{"time":701458,"text":"What's missing is a nervous system"},{"time":703273,"text":"connecting us to all of the things\nthat we design, make and use."},{"time":707915,"text":"What if all of you had that kind\nof information flowing to you"},{"time":711494,"text":"from the things you create\nin the real world?"},{"time":715432,"text":"With all of the stuff we make,"},{"time":716907,"text":"we spend a tremendous amount\nof money and energy --"},{"time":719366,"text":"in fact, last year,\nabout two trillion dollars --"},{"time":721766,"text":"convincing people to buy\nthe things we've made."},{"time":724644,"text":"But if you had this connection\nto the things that you design and create"},{"time":728056,"text":"after they're out in the real world,"},{"time":729807,"text":"after they've been sold\nor launched or whatever,"},{"time":733445,"text":"we could actually change that,"},{"time":735089,"text":"and go from making people want our stuff,"},{"time":738160,"text":"to just making stuff that people\nwant in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741618,"text":"The good news is, we're working\non digital nervous systems"},{"time":744429,"text":"that connect us to the things we design."},{"time":748365,"text":"We're working on one project"},{"time":750016,"text":"with a couple of guys down in Los Angeles\ncalled the Bandito Brothers"},{"time":753752,"text":"and their team."},{"time":755183,"text":"And one of the things these guys do\nis build insane cars"},{"time":758640,"text":"that do absolutely insane things."},{"time":762905,"text":"These guys are crazy --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764379,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":765439,"text":"in the best way."},{"time":768993,"text":"And what we're doing with them"},{"time":770780,"text":"is taking a traditional race-car chassis"},{"time":773244,"text":"and giving it a nervous system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774853,"text":"So we instrumented it\nwith dozens of sensors,"},{"time":777935,"text":"put a world-class driver behind the wheel,"},{"time":780594,"text":"took it out to the desert\nand drove the hell out of it for a week."},{"time":783975,"text":"And the car's nervous system\ncaptured everything"},{"time":786490,"text":"that was happening to the car."},{"time":787996,"text":"We captured four billion data points;"},{"time":790641,"text":"all of the forces\nthat it was subjected to."},{"time":792975,"text":"And then we did something crazy."},{"time":795268,"text":"We took all of that data,"},{"time":796792,"text":"and plugged it into a generative-design AI\nwe call \"Dreamcatcher.\""},{"time":801270,"text":"So what do get when you give\na design tool a nervous system,"},{"time":805258,"text":"and you ask it to build you\nthe ultimate car chassis?"},{"time":808723,"text":"You get this."},{"time":812293,"text":"This is something that a human\ncould never have designed."},{"time":816707,"text":"Except a human did design this,"},{"time":818619,"text":"but it was a human that was augmented\nby a generative-design AI,"},{"time":822952,"text":"a digital nervous system"},{"time":824207,"text":"and robots that can actually\nfabricate something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827680,"text":"So if this is the future,\nthe Augmented Age,"},{"time":831299,"text":"and we're going to be augmented\ncognitively, physically and perceptually,"},{"time":835584,"text":"what will that look like?"},{"time":837576,"text":"What is this wonderland going to be like?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":840921,"text":"I think we're going to see a world"},{"time":842654,"text":"where we're moving\nfrom things that are fabricated"},{"time":845746,"text":"to things that are farmed."},{"time":848159,"text":"Where we're moving from things\nthat are constructed"},{"time":851636,"text":"to that which is grown."},{"time":854134,"text":"We're going to move from being isolated"},{"time":856346,"text":"to being connected."},{"time":858634,"text":"And we'll move away from extraction"},{"time":861069,"text":"to embrace aggregation."},{"time":863967,"text":"I also think we'll shift\nfrom craving obedience from our things"},{"time":867758,"text":"to valuing autonomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870510,"text":"Thanks to our augmented capabilities,"},{"time":872439,"text":"our world is going to change dramatically."},{"time":875576,"text":"We're going to have a world\nwith more variety, more connectedness,"},{"time":878846,"text":"more dynamism, more complexity,"},{"time":881157,"text":"more adaptability and, of course,"},{"time":883499,"text":"more beauty."},{"time":885231,"text":"The shape of things to come"},{"time":886819,"text":"will be unlike anything\nwe've ever seen before."},{"time":889133,"text":"Why?"},{"time":890316,"text":"Because what will be shaping those things\nis this new partnership"},{"time":894095,"text":"between technology, nature and humanity."},{"time":899279,"text":"That, to me, is a future\nwell worth looking forward to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903107,"text":"Thank you all so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904402,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}